{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/eink-dashboard/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/d2602/display.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/ba381/display.webp 200w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/7f61c/display.webp 400w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/d00b9/display.webp 800w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/92f8c/display.webp 1200w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/fad48/display.webp 1600w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/b33a3/display.webp 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/e07e9/display.jpg 200w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/066f9/display.jpg 400w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/4b190/display.jpg 800w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/e5166/display.jpg 1200w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/b17f8/display.jpg 1600w,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/d2602/display.jpg 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/4b190/display.jpg\"\n          alt=\"The Display\"\n          title=\"The Display\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Another one of my lockdown projects...</p>\n<p>I've always like the idea of making an always-on display.\nSomething like the Magic Mirror project <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://magicmirror.builders/\" title=\"here\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>, or a productivity dashboard using an LCD display <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.jlwinkler.com/2017-05-25/raspberry-pi-productivity-dashboard/\" title=\"here\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>, but I also wanted something that is a bit more visible in bright light and uses a little bit less electricity.</p>\n<p>Hence, I settled on the idea of making a giant e-ink display that I could use to show whatever I wanted.\nUntil I saw <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://amzn.to/3iHGepG\" title=\"how expensive the panels are\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">how expensive the panels are</a>, and I settled on a much smaller <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://amzn.to/2E5lol0\" title=\"7.5\" e-ink 2 colour display\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">7.5\" e-ink 2 colour display</a>.</p>\n<h2>What does it do?</h2>\n<p>Well, there's a few modes (in case I ever get bored).</p>\n<p>Normally, I keep it in <em>weather</em> mode, whereby every 10 minutes it will update and show the following:</p>\n<p><img src=\"./display_weather_map.jpg\" alt=\"Weather mode\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Temperature</li>\n<li>Current weather conditions</li>\n<li>Rain chart for the next few hours</li>\n<li>Air quality</li>\n<li>Sunrise and Sunset times</li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"http://www.isstracker.com/\" title=\"The next time the ISS will pass overhead\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">The next time the ISS will pass overhead</a></li>\n<li>Weather radar of the UK <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/public/weather/observation/rainfall-radar#?map=Rainfall&zoom=5\" title=\"(just because it looks cool)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">(just because it looks cool)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I won't lie, the 3 hour rainwall forecast is nowhere near as accurate as <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://darksky.net/\" title=\"DarkSky\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">DarkSky</a> was, and the display panel I was sent didn't display red's anywhere near as vibrantly as other panels I have seen (I think it was just a faulty panel but I couldn't be bothered to pay for shipping to China and wait another month), but overall it's worked exactly as I have envisioned!</p>\n<p>There's also the <em>cowsay</em> mode, whose sole purpose is to present a random dad joke every hour, in the popular <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cowsay\" title=\"linux cli tool\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">linux cli tool</a> format.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/d2602/display_cowsay.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/ba381/display_cowsay.webp 200w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/7f61c/display_cowsay.webp 400w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/d00b9/display_cowsay.webp 800w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/92f8c/display_cowsay.webp 1200w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/fad48/display_cowsay.webp 1600w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/b33a3/display_cowsay.webp 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/e07e9/display_cowsay.jpg 200w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/066f9/display_cowsay.jpg 400w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/4b190/display_cowsay.jpg 800w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/e5166/display_cowsay.jpg 1200w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/b17f8/display_cowsay.jpg 1600w,\n/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/d2602/display_cowsay.jpg 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/2a756e6fe82e3c7ba3d9e63954d0c368/4b190/display_cowsay.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Cowsay mode\"\n          title=\"Cowsay mode\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>How to build it?</h2>\n<p>It's relatively simple, really...</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/d2602/display_pi.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/ba381/display_pi.webp 200w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/7f61c/display_pi.webp 400w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/d00b9/display_pi.webp 800w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/92f8c/display_pi.webp 1200w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/fad48/display_pi.webp 1600w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/b33a3/display_pi.webp 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/e07e9/display_pi.jpg 200w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/066f9/display_pi.jpg 400w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/4b190/display_pi.jpg 800w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/e5166/display_pi.jpg 1200w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/b17f8/display_pi.jpg 1600w,\n/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/d2602/display_pi.jpg 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/43d24584a51e788d03750d91cbdfab98/4b190/display_pi.jpg\"\n          alt=\"The hardware\"\n          title=\"The hardware\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You only need a few components: A <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://amzn.to/2DWrynQ\" title=\"Raspberry Pi Zero W\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Raspberry Pi Zero W</a>, an e-ink display (I chose <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://amzn.to/2E5lol0\" title=\"this 7.5\" 2 colour display from Waveshare\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">this 7.5\" 2 colour display from Waveshare</a>), and <em>something</em> to mount it all one.</p>\n<p>The instructions for putting it together are fairly self explanatory, so I'm not going to bore you.\nIt's just plug and play.</p>\n<p>The software is a little bit more of a pain in the ass, Waveshare have a <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://github.com/waveshare/e-Paper\" title=\"GitHub repo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">GitHub repo</a> with drivers for each of their displays, but no perfect method of building a UI for these displays, so the best way to push something to the display is in the form of a bitmap (essentially png) image.\nThe refresh rate of the display is a pathetic ~1 minute so don't worry too much about how long it takes to build that image.</p>\n<p>I have a repository with all the code for this project on my GitHub <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://github.com/jamesjarvis/eink-dashboard\" title=\"here\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>It makes extensive use of various API's, including <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.climacell.co/weather-api/\" title=\"Climacell\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Climacell</a> for the weather data, <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"http://api.open-notify.org/iss-pass.json\" title=\"ISS Open Notify\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">ISS Open Notify</a> for the ISS times, <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://icanhazdadjoke.com/\" title=\"ICanHazDadJoke\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">ICanHazDadJoke</a> for the dad joke service, and <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://helloacm.com/api/cowsay/\" title=\"This online cowsay generator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">This online cowsay generator</a> because I couldn't be bothered to generate it myself, although looking back it would probably have been easier to do it manually.</p>\n<p>For the map images, I used the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://github.com/openmaptiles/maptiler-toner-gl-style\" title=\"OpenStreetMap Toner\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">OpenStreetMap Toner</a> style tiles for the map and the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/public/weather/observation/rainfall-radar#?map=Rainfall&zoom=5\" title=\"MetOffice rain radar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">MetOffice rain radar</a> tiles for the rain overlays.\nI originally used <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://openweathermap.org/weathermap\" title=\"OpenWeatherMap\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">OpenWeatherMap</a>, but whilst it was good at global coverage of rainfall, it had very low resolution.</p>\n<h2>Next steps</h2>\n<p>I practically never do hardware projects and this has been super fun!</p>\n<p>I'm still thinking of ideas to use it for (if you have any ideas of a cool use for this format of display, contact me!)</p>\n<p>Ideas I've currently considered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"./predictions\" title=\"Coronavirus cases tracker\">Coronavirus cases tracker</a></li>\n<li>Public transit departure times</li>\n<li>Health dashboard</li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"http://www.dougswordclocks.com/\" title=\"Word clock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Word clock</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Another one of my lockdown projects... I've always like the idea of making an always-on display.\nSomething like the Magic Mirror project , or a productivity dashboard using an LCD display , but I also…","frontmatter":{"title":"☔️ E-Ink Weather Dashboard","date":"June, 2020","tech":["Raspberry Pi","Python"],"link":null,"source":"https://github.com/jamesjarvis/eink-dashboard","previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1200,"height":900,"src":"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/47498/display.jpg","srcSet":"/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/47498/display.jpg 1x,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/52258/display.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/de4dd2e7c934052cb52ec903fda205a8/50587/display.jpg 2x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/eink-dashboard/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/ipfs-web-hosting/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"📦 IPFS Web Hosting"}},"next":null}},"staticQueryHashes":["602281340","802641605"]}